{"key":"processedPost-17029018","value":{"id":17029018,"first":17009892,"last":17030344,"when":1350235423,"utime":"10/14/12 08:23 PM","content":"Soaking the grains hydrates them and also hydrates the bacterial endospores(if present).&nbsp; A soft, hydrated endospore will be killed in the pressure cooker.<br /><br />Excessive soaking is counterproductive because I've observed endospores under the microscope germinating and then forming new endospores within an hour or two.&nbsp; Therefore if you soak too long, you end up with more endospores than you started with.<br /><br />Detergent in the grain soak water is not necessary or productive.&nbsp; It's for straw.&nbsp; Don't confuse grain spawn prep with bulk substrate prep.<br /><br />The flaming in this thread is going to stop or the ban hammer comes back out, and it won't be rolled back this time.<br />RR","title":"Re: We can use detergents for straw... Can we use it also for grains after 24 hours soaking period ?"}}